255
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,110
It's work.

256
00:23:52,110 --> 00:23:55,140
Weren't you going to style me for the performance?

257
00:23:55,140 --> 00:24:00,950
Did you forget I am picky? A few samples will not do. Let's go together.

258
00:24:13,230 --> 00:24:21,070
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

259
00:24:29,650 --> 00:24:31,970
I'll pick you up at the store.

260
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:45,430
Sunbae Won's overseas training, has it been decided yet?

261
00:24:45,430 --> 00:24:48,890
He said he would think about it. Is this something to worry about?

262
00:24:48,890 --> 00:24:53,830
This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity. Why is he even thinking about it?

263
00:24:53,830 --> 00:24:56,700
Maybe he has a reason for that.

264
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,520
- That's a surprise.
- What is?

265
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:04,240
You... It seems like you really gave up on Won.

266
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:11,150
I mean, to be able to forget someone, there's nothing better than having them out of sight.

267
00:25:11,150 --> 00:25:17,190
My feelings are still the same, so I will miss him if I don't see him. But if he does the training,

268
00:25:17,190 --> 00:25:20,710
he can be far from Unni Ha Na.

269
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:24,070
Oh...

270
00:25:38,030 --> 00:25:40,670
Hello! You're here, Team Leader.

271
00:25:44,690 --> 00:25:47,920
Give me one that is most similar to the collaboration one.

272
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:21,780
How is it?

273
00:26:22,930 --> 00:26:24,980
Hmm, I don't like it.

274
00:26:47,310 --> 00:26:48,910
Yeah, Won.

275
00:26:48,910 --> 00:26:52,710
- When do you finish?
- Yeah, I'm almost done.

276
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:58,650
Okay, when you're done, come right away.

277
00:26:58,650 --> 00:27:00,970
Yeah, I'll be there soon!

278
00:27:16,810 --> 00:27:17,830
Won.

279
00:27:17,830 --> 00:27:20,490
Yeah. Here.

280
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:25,510
I thought I'd die from starvation!

281
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:29,890
Excuse me, Aunt! We'll have two orders of perilla samgyetang (beef broth) here!

282
00:27:29,890 --> 00:27:31,830
Yes!

283
00:27:31,830 --> 00:27:34,230
What is this? You didn't even ask me.

284
00:27:34,230 --> 00:27:37,590
What? You said it was good last time.

285
00:27:37,590 --> 00:27:39,530
But I didn't say I would eat it today.

286
00:27:39,530 --> 00:27:41,250
Let's just eat it.

287
00:27:41,250 --> 00:27:44,390
Why do you always do things your way?

288
00:27:45,670 --> 00:27:50,810
Ah really. Why are you acting like this too? I'm already dying from picky people today.

289
00:27:50,810 --> 00:27:53,670
Why can't you say anything in other places, but you complain to me?

290
00:27:53,670 --> 00:27:57,010
You're the one who is complaining!

291
00:28:03,550 --> 00:28:05,310
Let's stop.

292
00:28:11,090 --> 00:28:12,630
Stop what?

293
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:14,810
And I can't say anything?

294
00:28:14,810 --> 00:28:19,590
- Did you see everything that I did?
- I didn't see everything. Happy?

295
00:28:32,010 --> 00:28:36,470
How are you still not able to eat green onions at this age? If you can't use chopsticks, then use a spoon to take them out!

296
00:28:36,470 --> 00:28:39,250
What is it to you?

297
00:28:50,630 --> 00:28:54,360
You can't eat burdock either!

298
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:57,830
- It's that I won't eat it, not can't!
- That's worse!

299
00:29:02,030 --> 00:29:05,160
Why are there so many green onions?

300
00:29:08,770 --> 00:29:16,130
♬ Be mine! I love you, okay!

301
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,670
You're 34 now.

302
00:29:49,670 --> 00:29:53,550
That's why you're always tired because you wear those high heels every day trying to look good.

303
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:55,530
You have ugly feet too.

304
00:29:57,280 --> 00:30:03,080
Hey. What's really wrong with you? As a man, you're being so cranky because I ordered samgyetang without your permission.

305
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:06,330
Being all irritated all night! What about my heels?!

306
00:30:06,330 --> 00:30:08,250
This tacky and narrow-minded person!

307
00:30:08,250 --> 00:30:10,700
And! My feet aren't ugly!

308
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:12,390
Just take care of your nostrils!

309
00:30:12,390 --> 00:30:14,210
If you only walk properly, would I be like this?

310
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:17,140
Looking at heels where it's obvious you'll sprain your ankles,

311
00:30:17,140 --> 00:30:18,610
can I not even worry?!

312
00:30:18,610 --> 00:30:21,160
Worry? This is worry?

313
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,680
Are you doing this because you think I'll bug you after I sprain my ankles?!

314
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,860
That's not what I'm saying!

315
00:30:26,710 --> 00:30:29,990
Hey, Choi Won. You're always like this.

316
00:30:29,990 --> 00:30:31,970
What the problem is, what you're not content about,

317
00:30:31,970 --> 00:30:35,920
what you really want to say, why can't you just say them directly?

318
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:40,100
How can I know why you're acting like this?!

319
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:45,140
Even though I've seen you for seventeen years, I really don't know what you're thinking.

320
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:49,300
Aish! Ow!

321
00:30:50,970 --> 00:30:52,880
Aish, really!

322
00:30:53,910 --> 00:30:55,770
I don't know, really.

323
00:30:55,770 --> 00:30:57,530
Ow, it hurts.

324
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,870
You and I.

325
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:30,090
What is the matter, really?

326
00:31:37,140 --> 00:31:39,160
I'm home.

327
00:31:43,070 --> 00:31:46,920
What? Do you have something to say?

328
00:31:49,460 --> 00:31:54,990
I... went to your room to put your laundry away and saw that.

329
00:31:54,990 --> 00:31:56,690
What?

330
00:31:58,350 --> 00:32:01,710
The necklace. What is it?

331
00:32:01,710 --> 00:32:02,750
Oh...

332
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:08,150
Hesitating on the training, is it because of Ha Na?

333
00:32:10,460 --> 00:32:12,060
I'm not sure.

334
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:18,340
Won, even considering your seventeen years of friendship,

335
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:22,260
I think it is better to be away from each other for a while.

336
00:32:22,260 --> 00:32:24,190
You think so?

337
00:32:24,730 --> 00:32:29,630
More so, what you need right now,

338
00:32:29,630 --> 00:32:31,570
try to think about that first.

339
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:38,060
Okay, I will. Thanks.

340
00:33:02,270 --> 00:33:04,840
What is there to think about?!

341
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:07,620
What is there to be concerned about here?

342
00:33:37,970 --> 00:33:39,650
Are you sleeping?

343
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:41,410
Yeah.

344
00:33:41,410 --> 00:33:43,490
Are you really sleeping?

345
00:33:43,490 --> 00:33:46,450
Of course I'm really sleeping. Would I be fake sleeping?

346
00:33:46,450 --> 00:33:49,790
Hey. Why have you been acting like this all day?

347
00:33:49,790 --> 00:33:52,500
You don't even have a girl, but did you get your heart broken?

348
00:33:53,420 --> 00:33:54,840
Ha Na.

349
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,610
What is it?

350
00:33:57,660 --> 00:33:59,570
What are you doing tomorrow?

351
00:34:00,250 --> 00:34:04,250
I am going to sleep all day. A worker's golden sleep.

352
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:08,900
I'll call. Let's go shopping tomorrow.

353
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:13,310
Okay. Call me. Good night.

354
00:34:22,580 --> 00:34:32,460
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

355
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:45,590
So we are forgetting about yesterday?

356
00:34:45,590 --> 00:34:47,250
Did something happen yesterday?

357
00:34:47,250 --> 00:34:50,310
Without a doubt, simple. So simple.

358
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:59,150
It's already been 34 years since my mom and dad married.

359
00:34:59,150 --> 00:35:02,460
That's saying how old you are too.

360
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:09,230
Thirty-four years. Don't you think there are some old stories?

361
00:35:09,230 --> 00:35:12,430
It's not easy being together for a long time.

362
00:35:12,430 --> 00:35:17,020
There must be none of that heart-fluttering and trying to look good for each other.

363
00:35:17,020 --> 00:35:19,520
Being comfortable and dependable,

364
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:21,840
feeling empty without one another,

365
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:25,140
not knowing if it's good to have the other,

366
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,260
wouldn't that be how they feel?

367
00:35:27,260 --> 00:35:29,880
Why won't they know if it is good? Can't you tell by looking?

368
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:32,990
The two are the happiest when the they are together.

369
00:35:32,990 --> 00:35:37,600
And this doesn't suit her well. We are not buying your stuff. Why are you trying to see if it looks good on you?

370
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:40,570
Hey Choi Won!

371
00:35:41,910 --> 00:35:44,050
I want to buy them this.

372
00:35:44,050 --> 00:35:46,060
Everything started to look slow for me.

373
00:35:49,500 --> 00:35:53,720
Wow, what is this? It's so pretty!

374
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:54,910
Do you like it?

375
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:56,770
It was custom ordered.

376
00:35:56,770 --> 00:36:00,000
Special shoes!

377
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:05,390
Wow, it's totally my style, the way it is so fancy!

378
00:36:05,390 --> 00:36:07,320
It's too flashy for Mom to wear.

379
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:13,080
Hey. You can always style everything to go with the shoes!

380
00:36:14,430 --> 00:36:18,590
Looking at this, I think I need to buy more stuff.

381
00:36:18,590 --> 00:36:21,100
Don't you think so, honey?

382
00:36:21,100 --> 00:36:25,750
That's why I think you should never be given gifts at all.

383
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:27,300
Dad, do you like it?

384
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:31,720
I mean, I like anything my daughter gives me.

385
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:38,540
For me, to capture memories of you two for a long time, a camera.

386
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:46,520
Pictures are good. Then all we have to do is live happily for a long time!

387
00:36:48,850 --> 00:36:50,470
I spent some money too.

388
00:36:50,470 --> 00:36:52,190
What is this?

389
00:36:54,620 --> 00:36:57,370
Jeju island?

390
00:36:57,370 --> 00:37:00,070
Oh Dae Bok. Did you ask a favor from Won?

391
00:37:00,070 --> 00:37:01,940
Hey, how can you ask a favor for a gift!

392
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:06,480
I mean, Hyung Won isn't a stranger to us. Since he works at an airline, I could ask them for free.

393
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:12,090
Free? Hey. If he wants tickets, he has to get them with his own money!

394
00:37:12,090 --> 00:37:14,380
This gift from Dae Bok,

395
00:37:14,380 --> 00:37:17,960
I just need to be thankful to Won then.

396
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:21,640
Or should we get a refund?

397
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:27,650
Why are you fussing about money? Don't worry about it. Just go and enjoy your vacation.

398
00:37:27,650 --> 00:37:29,570
Can we do that?

399
00:37:29,570 --> 00:37:32,200
Of course!

400
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:33,700
I'm hungry! Give me food!

401
00:37:33,700 --> 00:37:37,610
Alright! Then...

402
00:37:37,610 --> 00:37:40,880
As a token for getting two gifts from you,

403
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:44,070
I will make something that Won likes!

404
00:37:44,070 --> 00:37:46,700
Yeah!

405
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:56,440
Cheers!

406
00:38:00,790 --> 00:38:03,180
I'll escort them the day they go to Jeju.

407
00:38:03,180 --> 00:38:04,800
Don't you have such a great friend?

408
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:08,500
Yeah. I'm so happy to have one.

409
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:12,960
I think I like your mom and dad too much.

410
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:15,340
I feel this every time we eat dinner, but

411
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:20,200
I'm so happy that I can fit in with the family eating and laughing all together.

412
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:23,450
If you're not there, it's more weird.

413
00:38:28,390 --> 00:38:31,330
I got an opportunity for overseas training.

414
00:38:31,330 --> 00:38:37,700
Oh, Choi Won! Didn't you say only aces of your company get the opportunity?

415
00:38:37,700 --> 00:38:38,560
Yes.

416
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:44,520
Wow, good for you! You should go! It's a really good opportunity!

417
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,610
How long are you there for?

418
00:38:47,410 --> 00:38:48,730
Two years.

419
00:38:48,730 --> 00:38:53,010
Two years?! Isn't that a really long time?

420
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:55,930
How do you think it'll be without me for two years?

421
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:59,320
I guess I'll be super bored.

422
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:02,390
I don't have anyone to bother me in the middle of the night.

423
00:39:02,390 --> 00:39:04,180
There would be no reason to go to our hideout.

424
00:39:04,180 --> 00:39:08,410
There's no reason to worry about getting fat from eating late-night snacks.

425
00:39:08,410 --> 00:39:10,520
Are you saying it'll be better without me?

426
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:16,390
No! But if I think about it, for seventeen years,

427
00:39:16,390 --> 00:39:20,680
besides you going to the army, there wasn't a time we were away from each other for a long time, right?

428
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:23,410
Even back then, I'd go visit every chance I got.

429
00:39:24,230 --> 00:39:25,610
Would it be the same as then?

430
00:39:25,610 --> 00:39:27,910
That, I don't even know.

431
00:39:28,910 --> 00:39:32,750
Anyway, go without worrying about me.

432
00:39:32,750 --> 00:39:38,480
If this is really good for you, being bored is easy.

433
00:39:45,090 --> 00:39:48,470
What was that? What do you know that you're shaking your head?

434
00:39:48,470 --> 00:39:51,580
I... know everything.

435
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,890
Cheers!

436
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:13,440
You're all set to go?

437
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:14,360
Won!

438
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:17,660
Please get in.

439
00:40:20,020 --> 00:40:21,800
Please take care!

440
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,660
Look after the house well.

441
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:25,760
I'll be back.

442
00:40:30,680 --> 00:40:32,560
Oh yeah! Freedom!

443
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:35,200
Here are your boarding passes.

444
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:36,560
Please have a wonderful vacation.

445
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:39,660
Such a dependable flight guy!

446
00:40:39,660 --> 00:40:43,340
It's a full course even with the flight schedule! Thank you!

447
00:40:43,340 --> 00:40:44,840
Go on inside and do your work.

448
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:47,040
Yes. Ah, right.

449
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:49,980
Before you go, should I take a picture of you as a wedding anniversary memento?

450
00:40:49,980 --> 00:40:53,000
Right, right. Let's do that, Honey.

451
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:55,880
Where is the camera that Won brought?

452
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:59,040
Here.

453
00:40:59,740 --> 00:41:02,940
Alright. Look here and be more affectionate.

454
00:41:02,940 --> 00:41:05,920
Cheese!

455
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:15,520
What? How can you work with that man?

456
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:18,300
Such a cold woman. Cold woman.

457
00:41:18,300 --> 00:41:19,760
Are you okay?

458
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:23,820
I have to do it. My reasons for not doing it have been blocked on all fronts.

459
00:41:23,820 --> 00:41:25,640
Hey, how is that possible!

460
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:29,800
Tell them you won't do it, and freely let it out that you don't want to see that bastard again!

461
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:32,660
Hey, do you think she doesn't know that?

462
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:35,960
A man who left like that, and came back all of a sudden,

463
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:40,720
and then you have to work with him for a few months. Ugh, that's even difficult for me.

464
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:44,420
And, what has he been doing this whole time only to appear now? And  then what?

465
00:41:44,420 --> 00:41:46,400
A collaboration?

466
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:48,180
What nonsense is he spouting?

467
00:41:48,180 --> 00:41:50,120
He says sorry for keeping me waiting.

468
00:41:50,120 --> 00:41:53,360
Crazy bastard! Coming back after three years and then what? Sorry?

469
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:55,660
Tell him never mind! Who said you waited?

470
00:41:55,660 --> 00:41:58,080
Maybe he had a reason for not being able to come.

471
00:41:58,080 --> 00:42:00,440
Reason? What reason?

472
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:03,280
Did he break a leg in an accident on the way there?

473
00:42:03,280 --> 00:42:05,640
Hey Oh Ha Na. Come to your senses!

474
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:08,160
What does he want now, after appearing again?

475
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:12,890
Hey, you stay still. So what about you?

476
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:19,320
What do you mean? I'm going to continue to work hard.

477
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:22,520
This is a really important project for our company.

478
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:26,860
Cha Seo Hoo is like a heel I have to sell.

479
00:42:28,540 --> 00:42:31,710
I just wish it would be over already.

480
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:40,000
Team leader Oh. You have to come to the theater right now.

481
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:42,240
I think there is a problem with Cha Seo Hoo's recital.

482
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:43,880
What?!

483
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:58,660
Did you plan this to disgrace me?

484
00:42:58,660 --> 00:43:00,380
I'm sorry, Teacher.

485
00:43:00,380 --> 00:43:04,200
If you change the sponsor that has been arranged for you on my credit,

486
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:06,340
you can't perform for the rest of your life.

487
00:43:06,340 --> 00:43:08,060
I am not changing them.

488
00:43:08,060 --> 00:43:11,440
All this time, I followed through with every performance the company and the sponsors demanded from me.

489
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:16,080
I am just refusing the method of them unilaterally not considering the performance location's schedule and condition.

490
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:19,300
You can't refuse like this.

491
00:43:22,140 --> 00:43:24,040
I'm Cha Seo Hoo.

492
00:43:34,540 --> 00:43:38,140
Hello. I'm Oh Ha Na.

493
00:43:38,140 --> 00:43:39,920
Sit down.

494
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:45,180
I understand what you're saying.

495
00:43:45,180 --> 00:43:47,860
I'll talk to you again after you come back from America.

496
00:43:47,860 --> 00:43:51,860
After causing trouble, and all that's been said and done, what's the point of talking again?

497
00:43:51,860 --> 00:43:54,960
- When the same thing happened three years ago—
- I do not want to talk about that.

498
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,580
What do you mean stop it? You wanted to go to a measly engagement ceremony.

499
00:43:57,580 --> 00:44:01,480
- You made such a mess that I had to take care of.
- Sir!

500
00:44:12,780 --> 00:44:18,220
What you said about going to the engagement ceremony... What do you mean?

501
00:44:18,220 --> 00:44:22,180
It's as I said. I went.

502
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:27,040
You were pretty.

503
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:31,940
If I saw you before you cried, it would've been nice.

504
00:44:34,180 --> 00:44:36,440
At our engagement ceremony,

505
00:44:37,380 --> 00:44:39,580
are you saying you came?

506
00:44:41,260 --> 00:44:44,160
Yeah. Even though it was late.

507
